ng plan gives  percent of lightsquared to cerberus capital management lp fortress investment group llc and jpmorgan chase  co leaving falcone with  percent of the companys equity in march  a judge approved harbinger capitals restructuring plan of lightsquared which pays off lender charlie ergen putting lightsquared in the hands of investors in november  falcone announced his resignation as chief executive and chairman from harbinger group hrg whose second biggest shareholder is harbinger capital falcone was paid a lumpsum of  million upon his resignation in march  the lawsuit accusing falcone and harbinger capital partners of misleading investors about the firms stake in lightsquared inc was dismissed the firms hedge funds include the harbinger capital partners master fund the credit distressed blueline fund and harbinger capital partners special situations fund according to press accounts the assets under management at harbinger peaked at  billion in  and had declined to approximately  billion as of  due to sizeable investor redemptions with approximately  of that total approximately  billion concentrated in investments related to building a highspeed wireless network in the united states historyedit harbinger was founded in  by its senior managing director philip falcone and harbert management corporation a birmingham alabamabased investment company that provided much of the original funding harbinger had funds under management of  billion £ billion as of the end of june  in  harbinger acquired the ownership of its funds from harbert although harbert handled administrative functions for harbinger for a short transitional period also in  harbinger acquired controlling stock of the zapata corporation from the glazer family and changed its name to the harbinger group inc nyse hrg the hedge fund is based in new york new york harbinger has owned large stakes in the new york times company clevelandcliffs and  stock ownership of satellite communications company inmarsat the company has also owned stakes in rival satellite operators skyterra and terrestar and british sugar producer tate  lyle in  harbinger capital was ranked th on the wall street journals the hedge fund  list pulling in  percent in threeyear annualized returns in  harbinger capital was ranked th on the wall street journals top  hedge funds list pulling in  percent in threeyear annualized returns harbinger capital which owned russell hobbs merged it with spectrum brands on june   for  million and now controls approximately  of the appliance maker spectrum top equity holdingsedit as of  the top equity holdings of the firm were in the shares of the following companies spectrum brands inc harbinger group inc north american energy partners inc and exco resources inc sec settlementedit in august  the firm reached a settlement with the sec agreeing to pay more than  million and admit wrongdoing as part of the settlement harbinger senior managing director philip falcone was also barred from the securities industry for at least five years but did not prohibit him from working as an officer or director of a public company among the secs multiple allegations were that falcone misused fund assets and diverted fund assets for personal use that the fund engaged in redemption and other practices that favored certain investors over others and that fund attempted to conduct an improper short squeeze on the bonds of canadian manufacturing firm partially in retaliation against a competitor investment firm harbinger and falcone largely admitted to these allegations in the settlement july   the us security and exchange commissions office of the whistleblower issued a final order in matter number   ruling that rejected a claim made by an individual requesting a reward for assisting in the investigation the sec rejected the claim asserting in the claimant did not provide information that led to the successful enforcement and denying the application see alsoedit harbert management corporation hrg group referencesedit  a b foley stephen hands up if you made billions of dollars out of the credit crisis the independent retrieved  august    a b harbinger capital partners llc  investor profile hedge tracker retrieved  april    herbstbayliss svea  november  falcone makes big bet on food products reuters retrieved  april    burton katherine jpmorgan renaissance trail hedgefund gains in  bloomberg lp retrieved  august    our investor lightsquared retrieved  august    checkler joseph  july  lightsquared unveils plan led by cerberus fortress jpmorgan denver post retrieved  april    checkler joseph corrigan tom judge approves lightsquared’s restructuring proposal wall street journal retrieved  april    vardi nathan  november  phil falcone resigns from harbinger group collects  million forbes retrieved  april    goldstein matthew  november  philip falcone hedge fund chief in exile is stepping down new york times retrieved  april    van voris bob harbinger investor suit over lightsquared dismissed by judge  march  bloomberg business retrieved  april    harbinger capital partners hedge tracker retrieved  august    lisa falcone who you calling wife of business week september   retrieved  august    a b company overview of harbinger capital partners llc bloomberg lp retrieved  april    harbinger capital imposes limits on withdrawals financial times january   retrieved  august    a b httpbusinesstimesonlinecouktolbusinessindustrysectorsbankingandfinancearticleece  weiss miles june   manchester united owner glazer turns to falcone bloomberg lp retrieved  august    the hedge fund  pdf wall street journal retrieved  april    top  hedge funds pdf wall street journal retrieved  april    chung juliet checkler joseph  november  falcone to depart harbinger group focus on separate company wall street journal retrieved  april    philip falcone and harbinger capital agree to settlement securities  exchange commission retrieved  august    order administering ceaseanddesist procee